cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using a hand-held camera to extract contextual information from the scene and perform semantic segmentation. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses modeling the spatial and temporal behavior of objects in the scene using a spatio-temporal graph, which is relevant to robotics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the system learns to minimize a cost function over the spatial and temporal object attributes to identify the most walkable direction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of an encoder-decoder architecture for semantic segmentation and the learning of a cost function. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is unlikely as there is no mention of cryptography or security in the paper.
